Tau continued his rich vein of form in Europe as he stepped off the bench to score the opener after rounding the goalkeeper in the 75th minute, before grabbing two assists as the Blauw-Zwart advanced to the last-16 of the Cup competition. The 25-year-old attacker, who is on loan from English Premier League side Brighton, has now scored an impressive three goals while grabbing three assists in nine appearances so far this season. The former Mamelodi Sundowns player missed out on making his Champions League debut last week against Galatasaray but will be hoping his impressive form will see him selected to face Spanish giants Real Madrid on Tuesday. --News24--